					<person>
						<persName>Eichmann, Adolf</persName>
						<linkGrp>
							<link type="normal" target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000564"/>
						</linkGrp>
						<note>
							<p>German SS officer in charge of “Jewish affairs” at the Security Service from 1935. From 1941 he was the head of the
								Jewish Affairs Department of the Reich Security Main Office and he was in charge of deportations from various European
								destinations to ghettos and death camps. In March 1944 he arrived in Budapest with his special unit and they arranged
								the ghettoization and deportation of the Hungarian Jews. After the war he fled to Argentina. Israeli agents abducted
								him in 1960 and took him to Jerusalem, where he was tried and he was executed in 1962. </p>
