			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Erich Schön (later called Kulka), a Czech-Israeli writer and historian, which became a part of the “documentation
					campaign” in Prague. In 1939 he was arrested by the Gestapo and was later imprisoned in the Dachau, Sachsenhausen, and Auschwitz
					concentration camps. He describes the fate and murder of Jacob Edelstein and his family in Auschwitz. Edelstein was the former
					Elder of the Jewish Council in the Theresienstadt Ghetto.</p>
			</abstract>

